Basic Nulable(String) expressions.
-- hasToken: rows 1 and 5 have "hello"; NULL rows 2 and 4 must not appear
1
5
-- hasToken: rows 3 and 5 have "foo"
3
5
-- hasAllTokens: only row 1 contains both "hello" and "world"
1
-- hasAnyTokens: row 1 has "world", row 3 has "bar"
1
3
-- hasToken combined with IS NULL: intersection of token match and IS NULL is always empty
0
-- hasToken on absent token returns no rows
0
Nulable(String) consisting entirely of NULLs.
-- all-NULL part: hasToken must return 0
0
-- all-NULL part: hasAnyTokens must return 0
0
Nulable(String) consisting multiple granules where one granule is entirely NULL.
-- "hello" appears in granules 0 and 2; granule 1 (all NULL) is skipped
1
10
-- "baz" only in granule 2
9
10
-- all-NULL granule (rows 5-8) must not match "hello"
0
-- "world" appears in granules 0 and 2
1
12
Nullable(FixedString)
-- Nullable(FixedString): only row 1 has "hello"
1
-- Nullable(FixedString): only row 3 has "foo"
3
-- NULL row must not match
0
Array(Nullable(String))
-- Array(Nullable): row 1 has "hello"
1
-- Array(Nullable): row 2 has "foo" (NULL element is skipped)
2
-- Array(Nullable): row 4 has "bar"
4
-- Row 3 (all NULLs) must not match any token
0
-- Row 5 (empty array) must not match any token
0
-- hasAnyTokens: rows 2 ("foo") and 4 ("bar") match, so count is 2
2
-- hasAllTokens: only row 1 has both "hello" and "world"
1
LowCardinality(Nullable(String))
-- LowCardinality(Nullable): row 1 has "hello"
1
-- LowCardinality(Nullable): row 3 has "foo"
3
-- LowCardinality(Nullable): NULL row 2 must not match
0
Nullable(String) with preprocessor = lower(str)
-- Preprocessor + Nullable: row 1 has "hello"
1
-- Preprocessor + Nullable: row 3 has "foo"
3
-- Preprocessor + Nullable: NULL row 2 is not indexed and must not appear
0
-- Preprocessor + Nullable: absent token returns no rows
0
Array(Nullable(String)) with preprocessor = lower(arr)
-- Array preprocessor + Nullable: row 1 has "hello"
1
-- Array preprocessor + Nullable: row 2 has "foo" (NULL element still skipped after lower)
2
-- Array preprocessor + Nullable: row 3 (all NULLs) must not match
0
Some negative tests
-- Nullable(Int32): must fail (underlying type is not a string)
-- Array(Nullable(Int32)): must also fail
